** =org-roam-bibtex= :disabled:

I've disabled the package because it's in alpha and has not updated in 11 months or had a meaningful release in three years as of [2026-01-10 Sat].

#+begin_quote
Org Roam BibTeX (ORB) is an Org Roam extension that integrates [Org Roam](https://github.com/jethrokuan/org-roam) with bibliography/citation management software: [Org Ref](https://github.com/jkitchin/org-ref), [Helm and Ivy BibTeX](https://github.com/tmalsburg/helm-bibtex) and [Citar](https://github.com/bdarcus/citar).

It allows users to manage their bibliographical notes using Org Roam and access the notes in `org-roam-directory` via `helm-bibtex`, `ivy-bibtex`, `citar-open-notes` or by activation Org-ref `cite:` links and Org-cite citations.
Org-roam is a plain-text knowledge management system. It brings some of Roam's more powerful features into the Org-mode ecosystem.

[[github:org-roam/org-roam-bibtex][org-roam/org-roam-bibtex]]
#+end_quote

